com.mvohm.quadruple.test

Class TesterClasses.BinaryFunctionTester

  • java.lang.Object

      • com.mvohm.quadruple.test.TesterClasses.BinaryFunctionTester
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    TesterClasses.QuadOpTester
    Direct Known Subclasses:
    SpecificTesterClasses.StaticAdditionTester, SpecificTesterClasses.StaticDivisionTester, SpecificTesterClasses.StaticMultiplicationTester, SpecificTesterClasses.StaticSubtractionTester
    Enclosing class:
    TesterClasses

    abstract static class TesterClasses.BinaryFunctionTester
extends TesterClasses.QuadTester
    An abstract tester class whose descendants perform testing of binary operations with Quadruples, such as Quadruple.add(Quadruple, Quadruple) or Quadruple.divide(Quadruple, Quadruple).

    Implements protected methods:
    • TesterClasses.QuadTester.testOp(String[]) -- tests the operation with the given arguments and registers its result in the TestResults instance stored in the corresponding field.

    Defines abstract methods to be implemented by descendants:
    • performOp(Quadruple, Quadruple) -- to perform the tested operation,
    • findExpectedResult(Quadruple, Quadruple) -- to find the value that is expected to be the correct result of the tested operation,
    • findExpectedString(Quadruple, Quadruple) -- to find the string representing a value that can't be expressed as a BigDecimal

    • Method Detail

      • testOp

        protected void testOp(String[] dataSample)
        Tests a binary function on Quadruple.
        Creates two DataItem instances with the values of the operands, each containing Quadruple and BigDecimal equivalents of the corresponding operand, performs the tested operation with the operands and creates a DataItem with the result, creates a DataItem with the expected value of the result, then registers the result in the TestResults instance stored in the corresponding field using its TestResults.record(DataItem, DataItem, DataItem, DataItem) method.
        Specified by:
        testOp in class TesterClasses.QuadTester
        Parameters:
        dataSample - an array containing String representations of the input argument(s) of the tested operation and a string representation of the expected result
